
FOR SU , DO "SUDO SU", not just SU

Docker Change Default Drive:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/32070113/how-do-i-change-the-default-docker-container-location


To start Docker with Jupyter root access, run the following in SU mode
docker run -it --rm -p 8888:8888 -e GRANT_SUDO=yes --user root jupyter/datascience-notebook

Rename the container for future quick retreival:

################################################################
TO RUN Existing Docer in ROOT use: 
$ docker exec -u 0 -it <container-name> sh
################################################################

TO get Pyodbc:
Install :
apt-get update
sudo apt-get install unixodbc-dev
apt-get install pyodbc
(or)
conda install pyodbc

If doesn't work try the following:
sudo su 
curl https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | apt-key add -
curl https://packages.microsoft.com/config/ubuntu/18.10/prod.list > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mssql-release.list
exit
sudo apt-get update
sudo ACCEPT_EULA=Y apt-get install msodbcsql17
echo 'export PATH="$PATH:/opt/mssql-tools/bin"' >> ~/.bash_profile
echo 'export PATH="$PATH:/opt/mssql-tools/bin"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

ANd then restart the jupyter kernel

If Not, try the follwoing:
sudo apt-get update
ACCEPT_EULA=Y sudo apt-get -y install msodbcsql17 mssql-tools
echo 'export PATH="$PATH:/opt/mssql-tools/bin"' >> ~/.bash_profile \
echo 'export PATH="$PATH:/opt/mssql-tools/bin"' >> ~/.bashrc \
sudo apt-get -y install unixodbc libc6 libstdc++6 libkrb5-3 libcurl3 openssl debconf unixodbc unixodbc-dev

Restart kernel 
